<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<!--
    HSK patch: hide Wolfein crafting benches from the architect menu.

    Why?
    All Wolfein recipes have been rerouted to HSK weapon/tailoring/smithing
    benches via the per-class bench mapping (see About.xml). Wolfein's own
    `Wolfein_TableMachining` bench is now redundant — keeping it visible in
    the architect menu would confuse players who'd build it expecting to use
    Wolfein recipes there, but find an empty bill list (recipes routed away).

    Fix: PatchOperationRemove on <designationCategory> for Wolfein_TableMachining
    and Wolfein_ReverseResearchBench. The defs themselves still exist (so
    pre-existing colonies that already built them can continue to use them
    via the recipes that still target them as recipeUsers via WorkGiverDef
    fallbacks), but the architect/build menu no longer shows them as
    constructable. New players never see them.

    Mirrors the HSK_Disable_MendingStations.xml pattern from HSK-VFE-Ancients.
-->
<Patch>

    <Operation Class="PatchOperationRemove">
        <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="Wolfein_TableMachining"]/designationCategory</xpath>
    </Operation>

    <Operation Class="PatchOperationRemove">
        <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="Wolfein_ReverseResearchBench"]/designationCategory</xpath>
    </Operation>

    <!-- Wolfein has a duplicate of HSK's ElectricTailoringBench. Hide it
         to avoid confusion in the Production tab. HSK's own bench is what
         all the rerouted Wolfein apparel recipes target now. -->
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationRemove">
        <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="Wolfein_Electric_TailoringBench"]/designationCategory</xpath>
    </Operation>

</Patch>
